President Trump visited Nevada and spoke at a roundtable event where he discussed various topics, including the economy, tax cuts, regulations, and immigration. He thanked Dean Heller, a senator from Nevada, for his support in passing the tax cut and reform bill. Several individuals at the event shared their success stories and how the tax cuts have benefited their businesses and families. The President also mentioned his administration's efforts to renegotiate trade deals, revitalize the steel industry, and improve relations with North Korea. He praised the progress made in denuclearizing North Korea and bringing back the remains of fallen soldiers. The President expressed his commitment to strengthening border security and implementing a merit-based immigration system. He concluded the event by endorsing Dean Heller for re-election and encouraging the audience to support him.